		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> LOTR Q&A Rulings from 05/20/04<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.89)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617'>Enrique "Max of Tat" Huerta</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 3, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Hello All!!<br />
<br />
   Okay, okay... so that Trivia contest was not that well thought out. )= Sorry for all the confusion that was caused and my laziness in just posting the trivia without researching it first. Regardless, it was nice to see a lot of people enter the contest. I promise that the next time I do a contest I research it a little more. (=<br />
<br />
   Congratulations to Gregory &quot;Galliard&quot; Austin for being able to come up with the highest strength bonus from one copy of Honed. Gregory was able to achieve a total of +90. (See Below.) I do want to thank everyone that participated, there were many unique approches to this question. Again, I wish I had been more careful with it so as to make it a much simplier contest. I also want to point out that others were able to achieve higher damage +X totals, but in their explaination there was an error in their calculation which invalidated there answer. (Such as too many cards in hand or not enough vitality for exertions.)<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Card Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>hi, i have a quick question. if my friend has a warg rider with a warg on him out, and i put him on frodo, who has answer to all riddles on, and i add a burden to put the ring on, can he exert his warg rider to cancel that action? thanks a lot. [Spatula Ma]</b><br />
<br />
Yes you may. The Answer To All Riddles has a skirmish action in its game text. The Warg allows the Shadow player to cancle ANY skirmish action (even The One Ring) during a skirmish. You would still have to pay the costs (Adding a burden.) but the effects would be cancelled. This does not however prevent you from trying to put the Ring on again during the same skirmish. Eventually, you&#39;ll either run out of resistance or the Warg-rider will run out of exertions.<br />
<br />
<b>The card says: <br />
REGROUP: Discard 3 cards stacked here and remove 1 to discard a Free Peoples possession. <br />
<br />
It also says: <br />
Each time a regroup action discards an Isengard orc, you may stack that orc on this card. <br />
<br />
When you discard 3 isengard orcs from the card and remove 1, wouldn&#39;t they stack right back onto the card? Also in conjunction with Isengard Tender who reads: <br />
REGROUP: If stacked on an Isengard card discard this card and remove 2 to exhaust a companion. <br />
<br />
Could you keep removing 2 to exhaust as many companions as you want since when he discards he would stack again? [Alienboy] </b><br />
<br />
The default definition of &quot;discard&quot; is &quot;discard from play&quot;. Whenever a card says discard ??? it means discard ??? from play, unless specified from another location.<br />
<br />
The first action says that the 3 cards are discarded from being stacked on the condition. The second action does not specify a location for the discard. Therefore the second one is defaulted to mean discard from play. Since the first action does not discard the cards from play, the second action cannot be used to play them back on condition.<br />
<br />
<b>Galadriel, bearer of wisdom reads &quot;while bearing an artifact or the one ring galadriel is resistance +1 for each (elf) you spot&quot; What is the effect of increasing the resistance of a character when he is not the Ring-Bearer?  [Konos the greek]</b><br />
<br />
CURRENTLY there is no effect for a non-Ring-bearer having a resistance... currently. (=<br />
<br />
<b>Hi Enrique! There is a lot of contreversy going around Boromir and the choose action. 1. Boromir is the ring-bearer and have 4 burden and no wound. Is he able to fulfill the burden or do I have to wound him twice even if let say I don&#39;t wanna play anymore? Basicly, the question is can a ring-bearer have more burden than his resistance. 2. If the anwser to 1 is no, then what happen if I have Boromir with 4 burden and an armor? Since hypotheticly I can&#39;t fullfill none of the 2 option, can I choose either one? 3. If I&#39;ve the ruling ring on Boromir, and chose the wounding option, then I respond by putting the one ring, I take 2 burden or infinite burden? 4. If I&#39;ve Desesperate defense of the ring and choose the burden option, then exert Sam, Samwise the Brave to cancel the burden, do I have to add another burden or discard 3 cards anyway? Now my opinion. I came to the conclusion that the rule about choosing the option you can fully fulfill, wich was made cause of Desesperate defense of the ring because it was poorly worded, need to be refined. Can you put the light on this?  [Treeplanter]</b><br />
<br />
1. Yes, a Ring-bearer can choose an action that adds more burdens than his/her current resistance. For example you can play PATHS even when your Frodo has 9 burdens on. This will immediately corrupt your Ring-bearer and you&#39;ll lose the game. (Remember, in a tournament you can always conceed the game at any time, there&#39;s no need to corrupt or kill off your Ring-bearer like this.)<br />
<br />
2. The answer to #1 was yes, so you could still fulfill the add 3 burdens effect.<br />
<br />
3. Basically, when Boromir starts a skirmish you either grab 2 wound tokens or 3 burden token and apply them to him. If something else prevents or changes those wound tokens that&#39;s fine. The reason Armor does not work for this is because Armor prevents you from grabbing 2 wound tokens in the first place.<br />
<br />
4. Similar to Boromir, when you assign a companion with Desparate Defense of the Ring on then, you either line up 3 cards to be discarded or 1 burden to be added. When happens to those cards and that burden before they get to their destiniation is up to you. If you exert Samwise the Brave to prevent that you do not have to add another one nor discard 3 cards anyway. (Note: This is different than using Samwise the Brave to prevent the Burden to prevent Vision From Afar because for VFA the adding of the burden is the cost for prevention and if you prevent the cost you also prevent the effect.)<br />
<br />
<b>Hey! I have a question regarding Eregion&#39;s Trails. Say I am at site 6 and I use Second Level to make an Orc Soldier roaming, the Shadow player passes, and I play Eregion&#39;s Trails to make the Soldier strength -3 until the regroup phase, but my opponent uses Orc Guard to discard my Second Level. Does the Orc Soldier still become -3 strength or does the fact that he is not roaming negate the modifier? Thanks! [Telcontar] </b><br />
<br />
The Orc would still remain - 3 strength. Eregion&#39;s Trails takes a snapshot of the moment and only those minions that are roaming are strength -3. It does not matter is the minion is not longer roaming or if a different one becomes roaming later.<br />
<br />
<b>Hey again... i asked you about the pippin wobas question long ago. I met you at the vegas psq/pse you&#39;re a really cool judge. I have another question... The Black Flail says: bearer must be a nazgul. Skirmish: If the bearer is The Witch-King, exert him and spot a possesion borne by a character he is skirmishing to discard that possion. From your previous ruling on my previous question i am going to assume that you can exert the Witch-King multiple times without discarding their possession and then with the last exertion discard it. Is it possible? my friends are bugging me about this =). So as a clear example lets say there is a fresh Witch-King out with a Black Flail and he goes up against dermhelm with her sword can you exert 2 times without discarding her sword and then as the 3rd exertion discard her sword? (just to make him really huge) [Christian Na]</b><br />
<br />
<b>One more question for this week (i asked one earlier about black flail)... Say you have 3 nazgul out... lemenya (fotr), toldea (wraith one wings), enquea (fotr) and there are 2 black breaths in shadow support area and 1 blade tip... lemenya is assigned to smeagol (slinker) and toldea assigned to boromir (sod) and enquea assigned to merry (fts) and fp starts smeagols skirmish and adds a burden to make smeagol 5 str and shadow player skirmish action can he give black breath to any of the other assigned blockers like boromir or merry? (before smeagol wins and discards one of them) black breath says to transfer to a companion SKIRMISHING a nazgul... my friends are arguing that those skirmish hasn&#39;t started yet so they are not SKIRMISHING a nazgul but my logic is that they are all SKIRMISHING nazgul cuz they are assigned its just that you start one at a time. tough question please answer this one along with black flail thanks =). you rule Enrique. btw sorry about the poor punctuation/grammer =). [Christian Na]</b><br />
<br />
Woot, I think that brings my official fan total up to 2. (=<br />
<br />
1. No you may not. You must always (with few exceptions) fulfill the requirements of an action to the best of your abilities. You cannot play an action, but choose not to do the effects if it is possible for you to do them. The first time you used Black Flail you&#39;d have to discard the possession.<br />
<br />
2. Only the characters involved in the currently resolving skirmish are considered to be &quot;skirmishing&quot;. All other characters are either assigned to a future skirmish or are unassigned. Since Black Breath can only be transfered to a companion that is &quot;skirmishing&quot; the only valid target for your example would be Smeagol.<br />
<br />
Hi Enrique, if you play calculated risk drawing 3 cards and you pick up another calculated risk, can you play it and pick up another 3 cards or does rule of 4 catch you. If so, are you allowed to still add the threat and draw one card only? [Archery]<br />
<br />
Yes, this would call under the Rule of 4. You could play Calculated Risk a second time, but you&#39;re only be allowed to draw 1 more card.<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Game/Tournament Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>By Cards like: Crack into Ruble & That is no Orc Horn you have 2 actions to do. is that a must or can you just skip one of those. <br />
<br />
Crack into Rumble: <br />
Gandalf - Event <br />
Regroup: Exert 2 Ents to Liberate a Site AND discard a shadow condition <br />
<br />
That is no Orc Horn: <br />
Elven - Event <br />
Regroup: Spot 3 Elf Companions to heal a companion and liberate a site. <br />
<br />
My question is; can you play the card by using for example only the healing or only the site liberate or only the condition removal!? i hope you can help! :) [¥LotRTCG¥]</b><br />
<br />
Well, I&#39;ll try to help. (= You must always (with few exceptions) fulfill the effect of the action, to the best of your abilities. If the effect of an action gives you a choice you must choose the one you can complete. If you can not fulfill the requirement of an effect you must do as much as you can and ignore the rest. So if for example there was an effect that said &quot;Discard 3 allies.&quot; but there was only two on the table, you would still have to discard those two and ignore the effect of discarding the third.<br />
<br />
In the cases of Cracked Into Rumble and That Is No Orc Horn, you must complete as much of the action as you can. You cannot choose to Liberate a site but not discard a Shadow condition. YOu cannot heal a companion, but not liberate a site. However, if there are no sites to be liberated, that does not prevent you from still playing the action and getting the other effects. YOu can&#39;t choose to not carry out an effect just because you don&#39;t want to. (Unless of course you&#39;re given a choice of effects.)<br />
<br />
<b>Hi Enrique, <br />
<br />
Tricky timing question about the twilight witch-king and sting, bane of the eight legs. The witch-king is (for some reason) fierce and fights Frodo who has the new sting. Frodo looses (surprinsingly) but he&#39;s not overwhelmed and would take a wound. Can the witch-king exert to wound Frodo twice or would he be discarded by Sting first? What is the exact timing of all the actions? (is it: wound on Frodo, then witch-king response -2 more wounds on Frodo-, then sting response -discard witch-king-?) That may change the outcome of the game :) <br />
<br />
Thanks for your answer! [LaBaleine]</b><br />
<br />
The Bane of Eight Legs is a response to a skirmish about to end. It is not a Skirmish action and it is not a response to winning/losing a skirmish. For the most part is will always be the last thing to happen in a skirmish (assuming the Frodo or Sam is still alive). Here is why...<br />
<br />
A skirmish phase is made up of three parts.<br />
<br />
 - There&#39;s the beginning of the skirmish. This occurs when the Free Poeple&#39;s Player decides to start resolving this skirmish. Actions that take place now include exerting for a Rohan mount and Southrons that wound or add threats.<br />
<br />
 - The next part is Skirmish actions. During this part of the skirmish, both players may play skirmish events or special abilities. The effects of these skirmish actions may or may not affect characters in the currently resolving skirmish. Examples of these actions include exerting a Bounder, playing a Swifty and Softly during a skirmish not involving a Hobbit, and Faramir, Wizard&#39;s Pupil&#39;s game text.<br />
<br />
 - The last part of a skirmish is determining the winner and resolving all actions that trigger from winning or losing the skirmish. A skirmish does not end until all of these triggers resolve. Examples of these actions include, placing a wound on the losing character, Worry, and the twilight Witch-king.<br />
<br />
After all three parts of the skirmish have completed, the skirmish ends. Note: That just before the skirmish ends, you can play cards like Loathsome and Final Cry or use Sting, Bane of Eight Legs. These do not change the outcome (winner/loser) of the skirmish, and still occur during the skirmish phase. The END of the skirmish phase. Last.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
